1
00:02:40,760 --> 00:02:42,830
What are we going to do, guys?
Stand here all day?

2
00:02:43,160 --> 00:02:45,754
- What's the matter?
- Wait a minute! What's wrong?

3
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:48,156
Your coffee can
is blocking the road...

4
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:49,668
... and we can't proceed!

5
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:52,275
- Talk better, buddy!
- Talk better!

6
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:54,511
You are in the mood for talk
and É'm in a hurry!

7
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:56,472
Get your things
out of the way!

8
00:02:56,720 --> 00:02:58,631
Wait a second!
Ask us politely...

9
00:02:58,920 --> 00:03:00,717
"May l pass because
l cannot... "

10
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:02,712
- Hey!
- Take it easy!

11
00:03:03,080 --> 00:03:06,038
- Mind the store!
- Get lost!

12
00:03:06,760 --> 00:03:08,273
Go on!

13
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:12,117
Shame on you!

14
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:19,234
Get off, if you're a man!
Get off and É'll tie you into a knot!

15
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:21,958
Right in your eyes!

16
00:03:22,960 --> 00:03:25,758
- Shall É do it, too?
- É wonder at your delay!

17
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:36,560
Yes! Wait!

18
00:03:38,320 --> 00:03:40,550
Stop!

19
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:51,594
Clear the road!

20
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:54,550
Get out of here!

21
00:03:54,920 --> 00:03:56,797
Hold it!

22
00:03:58,200 --> 00:04:00,555
Let us through!

23
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:04,035
Go away!

24
00:04:04,480 --> 00:04:07,631
All right!
Ét's no big deal!

25
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:10,277
Let's go!

26
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:16,436
What's this fuss!

27
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:19,598
Let's go! That's
not the place for a barrel organ!

28
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:23,117
That's the place for a traffic
policeman to start his moves.

29
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:25,630
Where should we stand?
At a pedestrian crossing?

30
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:27,836
We'll go where wheels
will never get us.

31
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:29,155
Let's go!

32
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:04,518
Look at that! A barrel organ!

33
00:06:10,280 --> 00:06:14,478
- É haven't heard one in years!
- True. They're lost now.

34
00:06:14,840 --> 00:06:17,354
Who knows how
this one was left!

35
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:24,637
Do me a favour and move over.
We have a sick person here.

36
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:27,116
All right, sir.
We've stopped.

37
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:29,231
- They stopped them.
- What a pity!

38
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:36,599
Come here.

39
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:48,034
Petros! Look at that
five drachma coin!

40
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:50,038
- The old man?
- Yes!

41
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:54,678
Pavlos!
Give it a turn!

42
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:56,679
Well done!

43
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:34,599
É'm almost bent like a newspaper.
Wait a while.

44
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:47,032
Ét's quite heavy.

45
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:50,636
Don't tell me! É've been carrying it
for thirty years, É know it.

46
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:55,030
This must be what
they call "heavy music"!

47
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:59,270
- What will you have?
- Nothing. We'll just rest...

48
00:07:59,560 --> 00:08:02,791
- ... and then we'll go!
- Let us sit for a while.

49
00:08:04,680 --> 00:08:06,636
- Have a smoke.
- Is there another one?

50
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:08,154
I've got two more.

51
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:22,829
Petros... Athens is
kicking us out, brother!

52
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:26,311
It's like it's telling us
loud and clear.

53
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:30,559
"Dudes", it's saying,
"pack your minor and major keys... "

54
00:08:30,880 --> 00:08:33,713
... "and get out of here".
Right?

55
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:36,434
- Right!
- We artists are not appreciated...

56
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:39,792
... like we used to be
some time ago.

57
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:42,588
- Our work...
- What work?

58
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:44,871
- Our scam, you mean!
- Say what?

59
00:08:45,160 --> 00:08:47,116
Yes, our scam!
Because if you tell me...

60
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:49,476
"Sir, you're a lazy dog
and l've had it with you... "

61
00:08:49,720 --> 00:08:52,996
"you're asking too much
to make money doing nothing... "

62
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:56,630
... I'll say yes.
But my back is killing me!

63
00:08:56,920 --> 00:08:58,956
I've been carrying it
for six hours!

64
00:08:59,280 --> 00:09:02,477
If I'd decided to carry
furniture on my back...

65
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:04,711
I'd be making money...

66
00:09:04,960 --> 00:09:08,873
- At least 80 drachmas!
- True, but what can we do?

67
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:10,997
- Change profession.
- Change profession?

68
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:14,272
How can I do that?
And what would I do then?

69
00:09:14,560 --> 00:09:17,472
Become a doctor? If I were
20 years old again, I would!

70
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:20,268
You have all the time
in the world to change professions...

71
00:09:20,520 --> 00:09:24,354
... and do as you like.
But I can do nothing else.

72
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:28,111
I was born doing this job,
I'll croak doing this job...

73
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:30,231
- There's nothing that can be done.
- Yes, there is.

74
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:32,112
- What's that?
- We can take it...

75
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:34,908
adorn it with
roses and carnations...

76
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:38,237
violets and daisies,
take it up to the Acropolis...

77
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:41,199
let it roll towards
Kind Herod's theatre...

78
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:43,271
... and then see what happens.

79
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:46,398
What's the poor thing
done to you?

80
00:09:46,640 --> 00:09:49,200
- It's the world that's changed.
- We should change, too!

81
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:52,199
- Let's see what we'll do!
- I can't do that.

82
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:57,235
I can't part with it.
For me it's a living thing.

83
00:09:57,560 --> 00:10:00,518
I talk to it, Petros.
Just saying it, makes me shiver.

84
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:04,236
I talk to it and it talks back.
"Oh, girl", l say...

85
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:06,875
... "why are you sad today?"

86
00:10:07,160 --> 00:10:08,639
And I get a reply!

87
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:14,271
- Get out of here!
- Go to hell!

88
00:10:14,560 --> 00:10:16,915
There's no talking to you!

89
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:27,398
Don't set foot here
or I'll knock you off!

90
00:10:27,880 --> 00:10:30,348
Shame on you!
Being rough with the kids?

91
00:10:30,640 --> 00:10:32,517
- Welcome, Thodoros!
- Take a seat, Thodoros.

92
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:42,717
- What are you doing here, dudes?
- We're moping.

93
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:46,390
- There's no work?
- Not even a penny.

94
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:48,631
- Hush, We got five drachmas.
- Oh, yes!

95
00:10:48,880 --> 00:10:52,031
A "century" coupled with another
"century" gave us five drachmas!

96
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:56,029
You see, our music moves
very old people only!

97
00:10:56,360 --> 00:11:00,751
Why didn't give a recital
at the old people's home?

98
00:11:01,040 --> 00:11:03,838
- So there's no money?
- Nothing!

99
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:05,752
- Why are you here?
- What can we do?

100
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:09,237
Take the barrel organ
on your shoulders...

101
00:11:09,520 --> 00:11:13,991
... and go somewhere else.
There's money in the countryside.

102
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:19,036
Would you like to make
2, 500 drachmas each?

103
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:21,828
Go to Platania!

104
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:26,751
There's a church of the
Holy Mother up there!

105
00:11:27,040 --> 00:11:30,112
And the Holy Mother's miracle
will make us have money?

106
00:11:30,400 --> 00:11:34,234
No! Listen here...
There's a fete in two days.

107
00:11:34,560 --> 00:11:38,599
Even I will take everything
and go there to make money.

108
00:11:38,880 --> 00:11:42,839
If you're there too when all
the nearby villagers will come...

109
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:46,391
... your barrel organ
will bring lots of money!

110
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:48,517
How can we go
when we've got no money?

111
00:11:48,840 --> 00:11:52,389
How? On foot!

112
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:24,148
- My respects.
- Who are you talking too?

113
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:27,392
To the colleague. If it
weren't for barrel organists...

114
00:12:27,680 --> 00:12:31,070
... tortoises would be the
unhappiest creatures on earth.

115
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:33,079
- Come on...
- What is it?

116
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:35,032
Rest it here to take a breath.

117
00:12:35,520 --> 00:12:36,953
Easy...

118
00:12:40,920 --> 00:12:43,673
I'm like a swastika!

119
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:46,680
I can't stand up straight!

120
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:52,189
I started out like a man
and I'll end up crooked!

121
00:12:52,520 --> 00:12:55,159
- Take courage.
- Till when?

122
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:57,868
Till we get to the church.
There might be a miracle.

123
00:12:58,120 --> 00:12:59,997
The Holy Mother might perform
a miracle for us too.

124
00:13:00,240 --> 00:13:02,754
You know something?
It's cool here...

125
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:05,548
So why don't
we open two nice pits...

126
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:08,712
- To do what?
- To get inside and die!

127
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:12,310
Petros, I've told you that
an artist shouldn't get disappointed.

128
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:14,630
An artist?
What artist is that?

129
00:13:14,920 --> 00:13:17,480
I've had up to here!
As if we're artists!

130
00:13:17,760 --> 00:13:20,957
Just because we turn the
handle and it plays music?

131
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:22,719
That's what barrel organs do!

132
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:25,030
If it were a meat cutter,
we'd get minced meat!

133
00:13:25,280 --> 00:13:27,555
- You're not straight!
- I'm not?

134
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:29,313
- You're hurting us!
- Hurting you?

135
00:13:29,560 --> 00:13:33,075
You're hurting us and we
artists have suffered greatly!

136
00:13:33,360 --> 00:13:35,920
- I mean to say...
- Excuse me, gentlemen...

137
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:39,232
Could you please tell me...

138
00:13:39,560 --> 00:13:43,075
... is this the road
to Platania?

139
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:46,312
- Yes, colleague.
- Are you an artist too, sir?

140
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:49,398
- Yes, sir.
- A fete artist, too?

141
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:52,473
- Yes, I'm going to the fete.
- You're on the right road.

142
00:13:52,760 --> 00:13:54,591
Thank you. Good night.

143
00:13:56,160 --> 00:13:58,469
- Farewell...
- That's how artists are!

144
00:13:58,960 --> 00:14:01,520
- Poor soul!
- Let's go.

145
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:09,314
- What are you doing?
- I'll give you a hand.

146
00:14:09,560 --> 00:14:11,152
- Put it down.
- Why?

147
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:12,913
- Put it down, man!
- Why?

148
00:14:13,160 --> 00:14:15,310
Put it down, before
you drop a kidney...

149
00:14:15,560 --> 00:14:17,152
... and a dog grabs it!

150
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:19,391
Listen to me! If Pavlos
is going to come undone...

151
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:22,956
... he'll go in one piece!

152
00:14:23,280 --> 00:14:24,838
Are we going to talk?

153
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:04,829
Pavlos... the colleague
is eating!

154
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:08,160
Maestro! Bon appetit!

155
00:15:08,600 --> 00:15:11,114
Something that is certain!

156
00:15:11,440 --> 00:15:14,716
Thank you! Please, join me!

157
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:18,669
Thank you. We're going
to rest nearby.

158
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:21,235
We salute art!

159
00:15:41,320 --> 00:15:44,471
Colleagues! My turn to wish you.

160
00:15:44,800 --> 00:15:47,473
- Bon appetit!
- Don't wish for us.

161
00:15:47,800 --> 00:15:50,030
We'd like to have something
left over for dinner!

162
00:15:50,360 --> 00:15:53,272
Yes, that's true.
Goodbye, then!

163
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:55,670
- Goodbye, maestro!
- Goodbye!

164
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:58,594
Farewell, maestro!

165
00:15:59,240 --> 00:16:00,992
Poor soul!

166
00:16:01,320 --> 00:16:04,357
- That's an artist!
- Right.

167
00:16:07,080 --> 00:16:09,116
- Pavlos!
- What is it?

168
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:11,829
- The girls' school is out!
- Say what?

169
00:16:12,120 --> 00:16:14,190
- Look over there!
- Well, well!

170
00:16:25,920 --> 00:16:27,592
Hello, man! Bon appetit!

171
00:16:27,920 --> 00:16:29,751
Hello, handsome!

172
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:31,559
Petros, they're like locusts!

173
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:34,715
- Shall I tell your fortune?
- Don't tell me anything!

174
00:16:35,560 --> 00:16:38,597
You have a good heart.
But heart don't understand.

175
00:16:40,080 --> 00:16:43,277
You love everyone
but you can't find love.

176
00:16:43,680 --> 00:16:46,877
You have something on your mind,
something secret.

177
00:16:47,120 --> 00:16:49,759
I'm full of secrets!

178
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:54,551
- Your heart is burdened.
- Wrong. My back is!

179
00:16:54,840 --> 00:16:57,798
- It's the same thing, friend.
- No, it's not, friend!

180
00:16:58,120 --> 00:17:01,635
- Cross my palm with silver now.
- Now you're done for it!

181
00:17:01,920 --> 00:17:04,354
- What?
- That "silver" thing, l mean.

182
00:17:04,680 --> 00:17:07,558
If I had money, I'd have crossed
the bus collector's palm...

183
00:17:07,840 --> 00:17:10,195
... and I wouldn't be
communicating with nature!

184
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:12,238
Keep your arm short!

185
00:17:12,520 --> 00:17:15,318
Leave me alone!

186
00:17:15,600 --> 00:17:17,830
Keep your fingers
far from my pockets!

187
00:17:18,120 --> 00:17:19,872
- Give me some money!
- Give me some, handsome.

188
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:23,630
Come! Pay me and I'll tell you
what troubles you...

189
00:17:23,920 --> 00:17:26,275
... what you're thinking,
what's on your mind.

190
00:17:26,520 --> 00:17:28,476
lI know what's only mind!

191
00:17:28,760 --> 00:17:32,514
- I don't need you to tell me!
- You have money coming to you!

192
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:36,076
- To me?
- Yes, to you!

193
00:17:36,360 --> 00:17:38,351
- Where is that?
- On the road.

194
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:40,670
- Do you know the road?
- Pay me and I'll tell you.

195
00:17:40,960 --> 00:17:43,030
And if you know the road
why don't you pick it up?

196
00:17:43,320 --> 00:17:45,788
- It's waiting for you.
- Forget that.

197
00:17:46,040 --> 00:17:47,393
And you put the tomato down!

198
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:49,835
- There isn't any!
- Then give me a cigarette.

199
00:17:50,080 --> 00:17:52,719
- We don't have any!
- Can I have half a tomato?

200
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:55,912
Put the tomato down!

201
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:59,749
- Can I have some bread?
- You're a pain in the neck!

202
00:18:00,240 --> 00:18:01,719
- Here it is!
- What?

203
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:03,991
- The money!
- Where is it?

204
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:06,077
- It's the 8 of hearts.
- What's that?

205
00:18:06,320 --> 00:18:08,311
- Pay me and I'll tell you.
- Pay her and she'll tell you.

206
00:18:08,600 --> 00:18:11,876
- Give the money, you meanie!
- Here it is. Give me the change.

207
00:18:12,120 --> 00:18:15,795
Don't be nasty! Give me five
to learn where to find it.

208
00:18:16,040 --> 00:18:19,350
- Are you sure I'll find it?
- Absolutely sure!

209
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:22,518
Why don't we go together?

210
00:18:22,760 --> 00:18:24,910
And when I find it
I'll give you some.

211
00:18:25,200 --> 00:18:27,236
Don't touch the organ!

212
00:18:27,560 --> 00:18:31,394
- I'm just touching it.
- You're a strange one!

213
00:18:32,160 --> 00:18:34,958
Hands off!

214
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:38,829
Enough said, girls!
There's nothing here for you.

215
00:18:39,120 --> 00:18:42,396
We're in the same line of work.
We deal in money, too.

216
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:45,911
All right, you have no money.
Play a song for us to dance!

217
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:48,191
That's right,
so we can dance!

218
00:18:48,520 --> 00:18:51,193
Dance?
You're very courageous!

219
00:18:51,480 --> 00:18:53,755
- Come on, old man!
- Yes, old man!

220
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:56,992
- Play a piece!
- How about a belly dance?

221
00:18:57,280 --> 00:18:59,794
- Go on!
- No songs!

222
00:19:00,040 --> 00:19:03,316
Wait a minute!
You want a song, girls?

223
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:05,909
- Yes! Give us one!
- To dance to?

224
00:19:06,160 --> 00:19:08,196
- Yes! A belly dance!
- All right.

225
00:19:08,440 --> 00:19:09,919
Come here, Petros.

226
00:19:12,280 --> 00:19:15,272
That's right, put it there
so we can see it!

227
00:19:20,640 --> 00:19:22,278
Come on!

228
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:42,112
<i>A carnation behind the ear</i>
<i>and quile in the eye</i>

229
00:19:42,480 --> 00:19:49,192
<i>The pocket always empty</i>
<i>but the heart full</i>

230
00:19:49,600 --> 00:19:56,153
<i>A carnation behind the ear</i>
<i>who's qoinq to qrab it</i>

231
00:19:56,560 --> 00:20:03,238
<i>Your breasts are a tiqht fist</i>
<i>that shred silk</i>

232
00:20:03,600 --> 00:20:10,199
<i>Kick your heels, qypsy woman</i>

233
00:20:10,520 --> 00:20:17,312
<i>Kick your heels, qypsy woman</i>

234
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:38,714
<i>A carnation behind the ear</i>
<i>and a headkerchief on the hair</i>

235
00:20:39,120 --> 00:20:45,514
<i>Your mouth is cool, </i>
<i>your lips are hot</i>

236
00:20:45,960 --> 00:20:52,115
<i>A carnation behind the ear</i>
<i>a ciqarette in the mouth</i>

237
00:20:52,560 --> 00:20:58,749
<i>Where's your tent</i>
<i>so I can pick you up</i>

238
00:20:59,200 --> 00:21:05,230
<i>Make a turn, qypsy</i>

239
00:21:05,680 --> 00:21:12,233
<i>Make a turn, qypsy</i>

240
00:21:12,680 --> 00:21:15,240
Come on!

241
00:21:20,360 --> 00:21:23,432
Well done, girls!

242
00:21:24,160 --> 00:21:27,914
- Hey! Take us along?
- Can we come up?

243
00:21:28,320 --> 00:21:30,788
Of course!

244
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:33,152
Come on! Let's go!

245
00:21:39,880 --> 00:21:41,757
- Hey, Pavlos?
- What is it?

246
00:21:42,040 --> 00:21:44,634
Let's ask them
to take us along.

247
00:21:44,920 --> 00:21:46,797
- To climb up there?
- Yes, climb up there.

248
00:21:47,040 --> 00:21:48,234
Let's go!

249
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:50,917
Friend, why don't
you take us up, too?

250
00:21:51,160 --> 00:21:53,833
- It's at the limit.
- Come on, friend!

251
00:21:54,080 --> 00:21:56,719
Move it!

252
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:59,116
What can I do, honey?

253
00:22:03,520 --> 00:22:07,877
Maestro... if you were a girl
it would take you.

254
00:22:08,120 --> 00:22:09,872
Let's go, Petros!

255
00:22:18,360 --> 00:22:20,749
- Why don't we sleep a while?
- Why not?

256
00:22:21,160 --> 00:22:24,038
- There's no need to hurry.
- Right. It's just...

257
00:22:24,280 --> 00:22:26,316
- What?
- You know my habit.

258
00:22:26,600 --> 00:22:30,070
I can't sleep if I don't read.
What's there to read?

259
00:22:30,520 --> 00:22:32,715
Shall I give you my certificate
from the army?

260
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:36,879
I said reading
not studying ancient history.

261
00:22:37,120 --> 00:22:39,190
You're hurting us again,
Mr. Petros.

262
00:22:39,440 --> 00:22:40,793
- Here!
- What?

263
00:22:44,680 --> 00:22:46,477
That's better!

264
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:56,355
- Look what's happening in the world?
- What is it?

265
00:22:56,640 --> 00:22:58,676
It says, a shipowner's
daughter has disappeared...

266
00:22:58,960 --> 00:23:00,951
... and her father...
Here, read.

267
00:23:01,240 --> 00:23:03,470
I'll read so you can sleep?
You're joking!

268
00:23:03,760 --> 00:23:07,799
Read it. Her father will give
50 thousand to whoever finds her.

269
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:10,839
"Shipowner's daughter
mysteriously disappears. "

270
00:23:11,080 --> 00:23:13,992
"Fifty thousand drachma reward.
Fears of suicide. "

271
00:23:14,280 --> 00:23:18,114
lf I were a shipowner's daughter
I wouldn't runn away from home.

272
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:21,039
And if I were a shipowner
and you were my daughter...

273
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:23,919
... I'd pay 100,000
so you wouldn't return.

274
00:23:24,160 --> 00:23:26,958
Sleep, because we have
a long way to go!

275
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:52,073
Excuse me...
Do you have a light?

276
00:23:52,480 --> 00:23:55,313
- I do. Do you have matches?
- ln my pocket. Wait.

277
00:24:12,280 --> 00:24:14,510
- What's wrong with the shoe?
- Pardon me?

278
00:24:14,800 --> 00:24:18,509
- Your shoe.
- Oh... the heel came off.

279
00:24:18,760 --> 00:24:20,239
Give it to me...

280
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:37,349
What do you think?
Will be he able to fix it?

281
00:24:37,640 --> 00:24:41,235
We'll see.
Something may be done, missy.

282
00:24:44,360 --> 00:24:47,272
Maestro, another
artistic inclination?

283
00:24:47,600 --> 00:24:50,160
An artist cobbler, that is?

284
00:24:50,440 --> 00:24:53,591
You're lucky the young lady
is present!

285
00:24:53,840 --> 00:24:55,956
Never mind me.
Feel free to talk.

286
00:24:56,840 --> 00:24:59,638
- Am I tiring you?
- No, rest, miss.

287
00:24:59,920 --> 00:25:01,956
I'm used to it.

288
00:25:02,320 --> 00:25:04,675
- Where are you going?
- To Platania.

289
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:07,798
- Oh, to Platania.
- There's a fete there tomorrow...

290
00:25:08,080 --> 00:25:10,753
- And you're going to...
- Yes, "to".

291
00:25:11,040 --> 00:25:13,474
No one knows what will happen...
And you?

292
00:25:13,800 --> 00:25:16,075
I... I?

293
00:25:16,400 --> 00:25:20,871
Yes, if I may...
What brings you here?

294
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:25,193
Well... that is...
I'm going that way too.

295
00:25:25,520 --> 00:25:29,274
- To Platania?
- Yes... not exactly...

296
00:25:29,560 --> 00:25:32,950
- But that way...
- And how, if I may?

297
00:25:33,280 --> 00:25:35,589
- Your shoe is ready.
- You fixed it already?

298
00:25:35,840 --> 00:25:37,671
- Of course.
- I don't know how to thank you!

299
00:25:37,920 --> 00:25:39,148
It was nothing.

300
00:25:49,880 --> 00:25:52,269
- Well, miss...
- She's also going this way.

301
00:25:52,560 --> 00:25:54,357
This way?
Shall we?

302
00:25:54,600 --> 00:25:56,431
- Why not?
- Let's go.

303
00:25:56,760 --> 00:25:57,829
Let's go.

304
00:26:56,480 --> 00:26:59,074
Excuse me, miss...

305
00:26:59,360 --> 00:27:01,271
- Please.
- I meant to say, that is...

306
00:27:01,560 --> 00:27:04,358
... what brings a girl like you
to this wilderness?

307
00:27:05,320 --> 00:27:08,039
- What is it?
- A spring? I'll have some water!

308
00:27:29,960 --> 00:27:32,599
Who does she look like?

309
00:27:32,960 --> 00:27:36,748
That's what I've been wondering
all this time, man!

310
00:27:41,240 --> 00:27:42,639
- Oops!
- What is it?

311
00:27:42,920 --> 00:27:44,911
- It's the fifty grand!
- What fifty grand?

312
00:27:45,160 --> 00:27:47,196
It's him! The mysterious one!
The daddy! The daughter!

313
00:27:47,480 --> 00:27:48,515
What is it?

314
00:27:48,840 --> 00:27:52,037
There she is! Miracles do happen!

315
00:27:52,400 --> 00:27:54,789
Oh, Lordy!
It's the 8 of hearts!

316
00:27:55,080 --> 00:27:57,071
- What eight of hearts?
- Money on the road!

317
00:27:57,320 --> 00:27:58,719
The gypsies told me!

318
00:27:58,960 --> 00:28:02,669
<i>The qypsies told me, dear</i>
<i>They told me loud and clear</i>

319
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:06,037
- An unxpected salvation!
- I should give her money!

320
00:28:06,240 --> 00:28:07,832
- To whom?
- To the gypsy!

321
00:28:08,280 --> 00:28:11,113
Fifty grand drinking water!

322
00:28:11,760 --> 00:28:16,470
That's why she was stiff
when we asked her.

323
00:28:16,720 --> 00:28:20,030
Mother of God, miracle maker!

324
00:28:20,280 --> 00:28:21,599
- Have a care now!
- What?

325
00:28:21,880 --> 00:28:25,395
When she comes, don't ask her
"where do you come from?" and such!

326
00:28:25,640 --> 00:28:27,915
- What are you talking about?
- Don't ask her name, either!

327
00:28:28,200 --> 00:28:30,270
- Of course not!
- The sucker!

328
00:28:30,560 --> 00:28:33,233
And when we find
the first policeman...

329
00:28:33,520 --> 00:28:36,034
... we'll hand her over
and go to collect!

330
00:28:36,360 --> 00:28:39,591
We found a cheque in skirts
along the way!

331
00:28:39,840 --> 00:28:41,319
She's coming... laugh!

332
00:28:46,600 --> 00:28:49,592
Well, missy?
Was that refreshing?

333
00:28:49,880 --> 00:28:52,872
Yes, I was thirsty!
The water was cold, too!

334
00:28:53,840 --> 00:28:56,559
- Well? Shall we?
- Shall we?

335
00:28:56,840 --> 00:28:58,159
Of course, let's go.

336
00:29:00,600 --> 00:29:03,194
And you carry it
all the way?

337
00:29:03,440 --> 00:29:06,113
- How else?
- And it's not tiring?

338
00:29:06,440 --> 00:29:09,557
Miss, if you love the barrel
organ, it doesn't tire you.

339
00:29:09,840 --> 00:29:12,274
And if you don't love it,
it does.

340
00:29:12,560 --> 00:29:15,313
- Do you love it?
- Platonically!

341
00:29:42,360 --> 00:29:44,954
Tell me something, friend.
ls Platania far from here?

342
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:47,839
- Upper or Lower?
Let's get to Lower first...

343
00:29:48,080 --> 00:29:50,913
- Then we'll see!
- Three hours' walk.

344
00:29:51,160 --> 00:29:53,276
- Only. Thank you!
- Farewell.

345
00:29:53,560 --> 00:29:54,959
Opa!

346
00:29:58,800 --> 00:30:01,792
- It can't be that far.
- The man said so!

347
00:30:02,120 --> 00:30:04,759
Let's ask that one over there.

348
00:30:10,440 --> 00:30:13,637
Tell me something, friend.
How far is it to Platania?

349
00:30:13,960 --> 00:30:15,393
- It's about 6 hours.
- Lower Platania?

350
00:30:15,680 --> 00:30:17,398
- Yes.
- And Upper Platania?

351
00:30:17,680 --> 00:30:20,148
- About eight hours.
- Eight? We were told it's three.

352
00:30:20,440 --> 00:30:22,396
- On the mule.
- Oh, three on the mule!

353
00:30:22,680 --> 00:30:24,079
Hello.

354
00:30:30,960 --> 00:30:33,952
- You heard. Three hours on the mule.
- I heard!

355
00:30:34,240 --> 00:30:37,198
Why did he say on the animal?
Where did he see the animal?

356
00:30:37,480 --> 00:30:39,914
Who was he looking at
when he said it?

357
00:30:40,200 --> 00:30:41,838
Forget the jokes
and let's see what we'll do.

358
00:30:42,080 --> 00:30:44,150
Let's ask those people
to find out exactly how far it.

359
00:30:44,400 --> 00:30:45,833
- No, miss.
- Why?

360
00:30:46,120 --> 00:30:47,792
Because one said three hours,
the other one said six...

361
00:30:48,040 --> 00:30:50,076
... the third will say twelve!

362
00:30:50,440 --> 00:30:52,112
- It's getting dark!
- There's no way...

363
00:30:52,360 --> 00:30:54,078
... we can get to Platania
this evening.

364
00:30:54,320 --> 00:30:56,709
- Did you have to be there tonight?
- No, the fete is tomorrow.

365
00:30:57,040 --> 00:30:58,837
We don't want to stay
out on the road, man!

366
00:30:59,120 --> 00:31:00,997
Where are we going
to spend thenight?

367
00:31:01,280 --> 00:31:04,511
Don't worry, miss!
We'll think of something.

368
00:31:24,560 --> 00:31:28,473
The mattress is a bit stiff,
but it's just for one night.

369
00:31:28,800 --> 00:31:32,156
Don't worry about me.
I'm not going to sleep.

370
00:31:32,440 --> 00:31:34,351
- Why?
- Because.

371
00:31:34,640 --> 00:31:37,029
I'd rather spend
this night sitting here...

372
00:31:37,280 --> 00:31:40,272
Oh, no! Rest for a while.

373
00:31:40,560 --> 00:31:43,393
We'll be on the road
bright and early.

374
00:31:43,640 --> 00:31:46,473
Yes, but that's not enough
to make someone sleep.

375
00:31:46,800 --> 00:31:50,713
Perhaps but I know
I won't be able to sleep tonight.

376
00:31:51,040 --> 00:31:53,600
I may never sleep again!

377
00:31:53,920 --> 00:31:57,310
Or rather, I might
sleep once and for all!

378
00:31:58,760 --> 00:32:01,718
Of course, you don't know
what might be wrong with me.

379
00:32:01,960 --> 00:32:03,598
- How could we know?
- We don't know...

380
00:32:03,880 --> 00:32:06,348
- ... nor do we want to know.
- You might be curious.

381
00:32:06,640 --> 00:32:08,232
- No!
- Not at all!

382
00:32:08,560 --> 00:32:11,120
I mean... you might have thought,
"What's this girl... "

383
00:32:11,360 --> 00:32:13,669
"... doing all alone in the
wilderness at night?" Right?

384
00:32:13,920 --> 00:32:15,273
We, miss Katie...

385
00:32:16,920 --> 00:32:19,070
How do you know my name?

386
00:32:19,360 --> 00:32:21,555
- I didn't say any names?
- You did! You said "Katie"!

387
00:32:21,800 --> 00:32:24,268
- "We, miss Katie", you said!
- l said "Katie"? You're wrong!

388
00:32:24,560 --> 00:32:28,189
No, miss, you misunderstood!
He didn't say "Katie".

389
00:32:28,440 --> 00:32:31,238
You said, "a girl all alone
at night"...

390
00:32:31,480 --> 00:32:34,119
and the maestro here didn't
say "we, miss Katie"...

391
00:32:34,360 --> 00:32:36,749
He said "miss,
although we don't know you... "

392
00:32:37,040 --> 00:32:38,712
... "we're not curious
to know this and that. "

393
00:32:38,960 --> 00:32:40,632
- Is that what you meant?
- Yes, brother!

394
00:32:40,920 --> 00:32:42,353
Besides, the priest says
that in church.

395
00:32:42,600 --> 00:32:45,910
He says "Praise the Lord!"

396
00:32:46,320 --> 00:32:51,678
Why should we care? Right?

397
00:32:52,040 --> 00:32:53,917
Of course!
So you name is Katie?

398
00:32:54,200 --> 00:32:55,713
- Yes...
- Oh!

399
00:32:55,960 --> 00:32:58,349
Come and lie down, miss Katie.

400
00:32:58,640 --> 00:33:01,518
Don't worry about
falling asleep.

401
00:33:01,800 --> 00:33:04,598
We'll lull you to sleep
with the barrel organ.

402
00:33:08,200 --> 00:33:11,431
- This is your bedside table.
- And this rock is the pillow?

403
00:33:11,680 --> 00:33:14,274
- Just don't play pillow fighting.
- Never fear.

404
00:33:14,520 --> 00:33:17,353
- I can't even lift it.
- It's a hard pillow...

405
00:33:17,640 --> 00:33:19,551
... but we'll see if
we can soften it a little.

406
00:33:25,080 --> 00:33:27,116
Try to lie down.

407
00:33:30,640 --> 00:33:33,791
Great!
Are you all comfortable?

408
00:33:34,120 --> 00:33:37,510
- Let's say I am!
- Would you like anything else?

409
00:33:37,800 --> 00:33:40,917
- No, thank you.
- Then... goodnight.

410
00:33:41,200 --> 00:33:42,633
Goodnight.

411
00:33:47,320 --> 00:33:49,675
Didn't you say you'd lull
me to sleep with the barrel organ?

412
00:33:49,920 --> 00:33:53,674
- Right away! Maestro, I want you.
- What is it?

413
00:33:53,960 --> 00:33:56,918
Put that waltz.
And you know now...

414
00:33:57,200 --> 00:33:59,668
- Easy does it!
- Yes...

415
00:33:59,960 --> 00:34:02,793
- Softly.
- Yes...

416
00:34:03,080 --> 00:34:07,198
- Like a lullaby.
- Done!

417
00:35:43,440 --> 00:35:45,590
She's asleep...

418
00:35:49,880 --> 00:35:54,510
Man, first time I lull
to sleep fifty grand!

419
00:35:54,800 --> 00:35:56,677
Yes, but you almost
ruined everything...

420
00:35:56,920 --> 00:35:58,876
... with that "miss Katie"
you said earlier.

421
00:35:59,120 --> 00:36:01,395
I'm only human! It slipped!

422
00:36:01,600 --> 00:36:03,716
It slipped, but the 50 grand
nearly slipped from our hands!

423
00:36:03,960 --> 00:36:06,030
Yes, but we fixed it!
Didn't we?

424
00:36:06,280 --> 00:36:07,679
Wasn't I good
with the priest thing?

425
00:36:07,960 --> 00:36:09,916
Praise the Lord...

426
00:36:12,160 --> 00:36:17,837
She won't wake up now.
She's fast asleep!

427
00:36:20,560 --> 00:36:22,835
Shall we go to sleep?

428
00:36:23,160 --> 00:36:24,878
Why not?

429
00:36:38,800 --> 00:36:41,109
Boy, what a windfall!

430
00:36:44,960 --> 00:36:46,188
What's the matter?

431
00:36:46,560 --> 00:36:49,438
I slipped!

432
00:36:49,720 --> 00:36:52,234
- Why don't you get up?
- What for?

433
00:36:52,520 --> 00:36:56,195
I fell here, I'll sleep here.
If you said, get up...

434
00:36:56,480 --> 00:36:58,550
... to lie in bed,
I would accept that.

435
00:36:58,840 --> 00:37:02,913
But there's no reason to get up
and lie down elsewhere.

436
00:37:03,360 --> 00:37:04,918
That's right.

437
00:37:05,360 --> 00:37:07,510
Boy, what a windfall!

438
00:37:07,720 --> 00:37:09,790
- What windfall?
- The fifty grand!

439
00:37:10,080 --> 00:37:13,755
Do you know what fify grand is?
Fifty grand is...

440
00:37:14,200 --> 00:37:15,713
... fifty grand!

441
00:37:16,000 --> 00:37:17,752
- Isn't it?
- Yeah!

442
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:21,629
When we get it,
let's turn it to five drachma coins!

443
00:37:21,920 --> 00:37:23,672
- Five drachma coins?
- Yes!

444
00:37:23,920 --> 00:37:27,879
- What will we do with that?
- We'll count it every evening.

445
00:37:28,560 --> 00:37:31,154
- And we'll pass the time!
- Goodnight!

446
00:37:31,520 --> 00:37:33,556
Bona notte, maestro!

447
00:40:32,680 --> 00:40:34,477
Pavlos!

448
00:40:34,760 --> 00:40:38,514
Pavlos! Wake up!

449
00:40:38,840 --> 00:40:41,229
- What's up?
- Get up!

450
00:40:41,520 --> 00:40:44,034
- What is it? Telegram?
- It's the fifty grand!

451
00:40:44,280 --> 00:40:47,078
- What fifty grand?
- The girl! Eight of hearts!

452
00:40:47,360 --> 00:40:48,713
- So?
- She's run away!

453
00:40:48,960 --> 00:40:50,996
- She's what?
- She's run away!

454
00:40:51,280 --> 00:40:53,874
Why are we sitting here?

455
00:40:54,120 --> 00:40:56,509
- That's why I woke you up!
- All right, easy!

456
00:41:01,080 --> 00:41:03,878
- The barrel organ?
- Forget it!

457
00:41:04,160 --> 00:41:06,071
- The fifty grand is gone!
- Let's go!

458
00:41:08,720 --> 00:41:10,358
- Which way did she go?
- That way!

459
00:41:48,840 --> 00:41:51,354
Where the hell is she?
I can't see her anywhere!

460
00:41:51,680 --> 00:41:53,671
Let's listen!

461
00:41:55,120 --> 00:41:58,430
- What are you doing?
- I've seen it in the movies!

462
00:41:58,720 --> 00:42:01,359
That's who lndians
listen to horses.

463
00:42:02,480 --> 00:42:04,755
- Oh! Oh!
- Did you hear anything?

464
00:42:05,000 --> 00:42:07,468
No! An ant got into my ear!

465
00:42:07,720 --> 00:42:08,709
Get out of here!

466
00:42:26,120 --> 00:42:29,078
Where is she?
Vanished into thin air?

467
00:42:29,320 --> 00:42:31,629
Nah! She's on the road
going far away.

468
00:42:31,920 --> 00:42:35,196
No way! We'd see her that way.
She's somewhere around here.

469
00:42:35,520 --> 00:42:37,351
- And we'll lose the organ!
- Why?

470
00:42:37,600 --> 00:42:39,636
We won't find our way back.
We should have used breadcrumbs!

471
00:42:39,880 --> 00:42:41,711
As if we'd get lost!

472
00:42:42,000 --> 00:42:43,831
- How do you explain this?
- What?

473
00:42:44,160 --> 00:42:45,718
- Her flight.
- Who knows?

474
00:42:45,960 --> 00:42:48,235
She may have realised
we know about her.

475
00:42:48,480 --> 00:42:51,199
What was that church stuff?

476
00:42:51,400 --> 00:42:53,311
- You think that's to blame?
- Probably!

477
00:42:53,600 --> 00:42:54,669
Wait!

478
00:43:07,680 --> 00:43:09,830
What do you think?
Shall we use her name?

479
00:43:10,080 --> 00:43:11,479
Why not?

480
00:43:11,840 --> 00:43:14,195
Wait a second... Take a breath.

481
00:43:14,520 --> 00:43:18,433
- No shouting! Nice and easy.
- What do you mean?

482
00:43:18,720 --> 00:43:25,512
Politely. Watch me.
Miss Katie... miss Katie...

483
00:43:26,400 --> 00:43:29,392
Watch me. Miss Katie...

484
00:43:29,760 --> 00:43:32,228
<i>Miss Katie... </i>

485
00:43:33,120 --> 00:43:35,918
Miss Katie...

486
00:43:37,040 --> 00:43:38,792
- Man! I see her!
- You do?

487
00:43:39,040 --> 00:43:40,871
- Three grand from the fifty!
- Where are they?

488
00:43:41,120 --> 00:43:42,439
- There they are!
- Man!

489
00:43:42,680 --> 00:43:44,671
Let's surround her...

490
00:43:45,000 --> 00:43:47,833
- Let's go!
- Take it easy!

491
00:43:48,120 --> 00:43:50,190
- All right!
- Take it easy!

492
00:43:50,400 --> 00:43:51,594
All right!

493
00:44:01,520 --> 00:44:02,509
Oh!

494
00:44:03,720 --> 00:44:06,188
Long time no see, they say
Right?

495
00:44:06,480 --> 00:44:08,994
- What do you want?
- Nothing.

496
00:44:09,280 --> 00:44:12,033
- Do we want anything, maestro?
- What could we want?

497
00:44:12,320 --> 00:44:14,276
- Do you want anything?
- I want you to stop chasing me!

498
00:44:14,560 --> 00:44:16,755
- We're chasing you?
- Of course you are!

499
00:44:17,040 --> 00:44:18,996
Don't you think I saw
you running to find me...

500
00:44:19,280 --> 00:44:20,759
... like hound dogs?

501
00:44:21,000 --> 00:44:24,117
Maestro looks a little like
a pit bull but don't fear him.

502
00:44:24,360 --> 00:44:26,669
- He doesn't bite.
- If you're not chasing me...

503
00:44:26,960 --> 00:44:28,552
... as you say,
why were you calling me?

504
00:44:28,840 --> 00:44:30,114
- We called?
- What did we say?

505
00:44:30,360 --> 00:44:33,113
"Miss Katie! Miss Katie!"
Or is it the matins...

506
00:44:33,400 --> 00:44:35,789
... and you were chanting?

507
00:44:36,200 --> 00:44:38,839
You misunderstood!
If we were calling your name...

508
00:44:39,120 --> 00:44:42,032
it was simply to see
if you had lost your way...

509
00:44:42,360 --> 00:44:44,510
- Of course!
- I misunderstood, eh?

510
00:44:44,800 --> 00:44:46,313
- Of course!
- Very well!

511
00:44:46,600 --> 00:44:47,999
- I apologise then!
- Don't mention it...

512
00:44:48,240 --> 00:44:49,798
- Thank you for taking care of me.
- It was nothing, you're welcome.

513
00:44:50,080 --> 00:44:51,229
And goodbye!

514
00:44:56,320 --> 00:44:58,356
Why are you following me now?

515
00:44:58,640 --> 00:45:00,312
We're not following you, missy.

516
00:45:00,560 --> 00:45:02,152
- You're not?
- No!

517
00:45:02,400 --> 00:45:04,595
We simply happened
to be going this way...

518
00:45:04,880 --> 00:45:06,472
- Oh, so that's it!
- Of course...

519
00:45:06,760 --> 00:45:09,832
All right. Go your way then
because mine is this way.

520
00:45:38,880 --> 00:45:40,871
What now?

521
00:45:41,120 --> 00:45:43,236
- We didn't...
- You have nothing to say! Right!

522
00:45:43,520 --> 00:45:45,397
Rather all that's left to say
is the truth!

523
00:45:45,640 --> 00:45:46,959
Come on, then!

524
00:45:48,200 --> 00:45:50,270
To make things easier
for you... here you are!

525
00:45:53,600 --> 00:45:55,636
It fell of the pocket
of one of you!

526
00:45:55,880 --> 00:45:59,156
And it helped explain
your taking care of me!

527
00:45:59,760 --> 00:46:02,593
Well? What are you
thinking of doing now?

528
00:46:02,840 --> 00:46:05,035
How you will grab me
and where to turn me in...

529
00:46:05,280 --> 00:46:07,589
... to receive the
thirty pieces of silver!

530
00:46:07,880 --> 00:46:10,314
- Is it thirty now?
- Hush!

531
00:46:10,560 --> 00:46:12,471
Wasn't it fifty?
Let's not go back on that!

532
00:46:12,720 --> 00:46:16,429
Here I am now! Grab me!
Why so hesitant? Are you afraid?

533
00:46:16,720 --> 00:46:18,756
You have nothing
to fear from me.

534
00:46:19,040 --> 00:46:20,837
You're two men and
I'm just a girl!

535
00:46:21,720 --> 00:46:24,359
- Listen, miss...
- What's left to say?

536
00:46:24,640 --> 00:46:26,232
What can we all say?

537
00:46:26,480 --> 00:46:28,038
You won't convince me
no matter what you say.

538
00:46:28,240 --> 00:46:29,832
And nothing I say
will move you.

539
00:46:30,040 --> 00:46:32,918
You don't see me as a person,
but as a money bag!

540
00:46:33,160 --> 00:46:35,037
- You've got it wrong, miss.
- And I'm telling you...

541
00:46:35,240 --> 00:46:37,834
that if you read in the papers
the money would be 100,000...

542
00:46:38,080 --> 00:46:42,039
... to deliver my dead body,
you'd have killed me already!

543
00:46:42,360 --> 00:46:44,396
Is that the kind of people
you think we are?

544
00:46:44,680 --> 00:46:47,274
- Yes, that's it...
- I repeat what I said earlier!

545
00:46:47,560 --> 00:46:49,391
- You've got it wrong!
- Yeah, right...

546
00:46:49,680 --> 00:46:52,831
We are poor people
and for us 50 grand...

547
00:46:53,120 --> 00:46:55,918
... is like a magical dream!

548
00:46:56,200 --> 00:46:58,873
But even without the money,
as honest people...

549
00:46:59,120 --> 00:47:02,112
to whom fortune brought
a crazy girl...

550
00:47:02,360 --> 00:47:04,555
aren't we obliged
to take her by the ear...

551
00:47:04,800 --> 00:47:07,314
back to her parents
who are mad with worry...

552
00:47:07,600 --> 00:47:10,433
because she's gone? You think
that without the fifty grand...

553
00:47:10,680 --> 00:47:12,750
... we'd say "Let her rot"?

554
00:47:13,000 --> 00:47:15,753
And we'd have left you
all alone in the wilderness...

555
00:47:16,000 --> 00:47:18,389
- ... to be eaten by jackals.
- You've got us wrong, miss.

556
00:47:18,680 --> 00:47:19,874
The first thing we want
is your own good.

557
00:47:20,160 --> 00:47:21,798
And you think that
can be found at home!

558
00:47:22,040 --> 00:47:23,996
Where else?
In the glens and dells?

559
00:47:24,240 --> 00:47:27,596
You're wrong! And l'm no
the crazy girl you think l am.

560
00:47:27,880 --> 00:47:30,952
My leaving home
couldn't be helped.

561
00:47:31,280 --> 00:47:33,999
- Why not?
- It couldn't have.

562
00:47:34,720 --> 00:47:36,597
My father is
one of those people...

563
00:47:36,880 --> 00:47:38,871
... who see everything
in life as business.

564
00:47:39,240 --> 00:47:42,038
Ten days ago l was happy.

565
00:47:42,400 --> 00:47:44,072
I loved him and he loved me.

566
00:47:44,360 --> 00:47:46,555
Of course, he wasn't
a shipowner's son.

567
00:47:46,880 --> 00:47:49,235
But he was a good man.
Honest, educated...

568
00:47:49,520 --> 00:47:51,636
and he had worked
his way up to a good post...

569
00:47:51,880 --> 00:47:53,199
... in my father's company.

570
00:47:53,680 --> 00:47:55,591
<i>That eveninq, he had</i>
<i>walked me home. </i>

571
00:47:55,880 --> 00:47:57,836
<i>We hadn't said anythinq. </i>

572
00:47:58,120 --> 00:48:01,556
<i>While we were sayinq qoodbye</i>
<i>I don't know how... </i>

573
00:48:01,840 --> 00:48:04,195
<i>We ended up</i>
<i>in each other's arms. </i>

574
00:48:04,480 --> 00:48:06,232
<i>Suddenly... </i>

575
00:48:08,200 --> 00:48:11,192
<i>I lost my nerve, when</i>
<i>in the headliqht qlare... </i>

576
00:48:11,440 --> 00:48:13,795
<i>I recoqnised my father. </i>

577
00:48:17,680 --> 00:48:19,830
- Good evening.
- Mr. Benardis, I'd like...

578
00:48:20,120 --> 00:48:22,793
- To explain...
- Tomorrow, son. Tomorrow.

579
00:48:23,320 --> 00:48:24,673
Come, Katie.

580
00:48:25,720 --> 00:48:29,235
We'll talk in the office
tomorrow. Let's go.

581
00:48:38,280 --> 00:48:40,316
<i>He said nothinq at home. </i>

582
00:48:40,720 --> 00:48:44,349
Not a word! The following afternoon
when I knew father would be out...

583
00:48:44,640 --> 00:48:47,871
... I ran to the office to find Dimitris
and learn what they'd talked about.

584
00:48:48,440 --> 00:48:49,714
<i>What happened?</i>

585
00:49:03,280 --> 00:49:04,838
- Mr. Lambrakis?
- He was transferred, miss.

586
00:49:05,080 --> 00:49:06,354
To Patras.

587
00:49:06,600 --> 00:49:08,272
- Transferred?
- Yes.

588
00:49:08,680 --> 00:49:11,433
<i>When I returned home, there was</i>
<i>another unpleasant surprise. </i>

589
00:49:11,720 --> 00:49:14,280
<i>A colleaque of my father's, </i>
<i>another shipowner... </i>

590
00:49:14,560 --> 00:49:17,552
<i>who had often annoyed me</i>
<i>with his persistent flirtations... </i>

591
00:49:17,800 --> 00:49:20,519
<i>that I miqht consider lauqhable, </i>
<i>if I were not disqusted by it. </i>

592
00:49:20,800 --> 00:49:24,236
<i>He complimented me like a fool</i>
<i>and while he was droolinq... </i>

593
00:49:24,520 --> 00:49:27,478
<i>... he kept my hand in his</i>
<i>sweaty, soft palms. </i>

594
00:49:27,760 --> 00:49:30,593
<i>I tried to be as</i>
<i>polite as possible with him. </i>

595
00:49:30,920 --> 00:49:32,956
- Take a seat, Mr. Kordianides.
- Merci.

596
00:49:38,640 --> 00:49:40,232
I waited thirty minutes for you.

597
00:49:40,520 --> 00:49:42,431
I could have waited
half a century!

598
00:49:42,680 --> 00:49:45,638
I don't know if they told you,
but daddy will be late today.

599
00:49:45,920 --> 00:49:48,354
Oh, that's better!
We can talk about us.

600
00:49:48,640 --> 00:49:52,872
- About us? What do you mean?
- Listen, miss Katie...

601
00:49:53,320 --> 00:49:56,915
You must have realised
how I feel about you.

602
00:49:57,240 --> 00:50:00,755
I told your father about
my feelings for you today.

603
00:50:01,080 --> 00:50:04,277
And he made me realise
he wouldn't object...

604
00:50:04,600 --> 00:50:06,716
My father may not object...

605
00:50:07,120 --> 00:50:08,633
... but I do!

606
00:50:08,960 --> 00:50:10,916
You do?

607
00:50:11,480 --> 00:50:13,948
"Yes, I do! In a nutshell,
Mr. Kordianides... "

608
00:50:14,240 --> 00:50:15,798
"don't insist... "

609
00:50:16,040 --> 00:50:17,871
... "because you are wasting
your time and your breath. "

610
00:50:18,120 --> 00:50:19,678
- You told him that? Straight?
- Yes.

611
00:50:19,920 --> 00:50:21,911
- What did the dude do?
- What could he do, man?

612
00:50:22,160 --> 00:50:24,549
He put down his head...

613
00:50:24,800 --> 00:50:27,268
... and slunk quietly away. Right?

614
00:50:27,520 --> 00:50:28,714
Right...

615
00:50:28,960 --> 00:50:31,713
But my father is not the
person who gives up easily.

616
00:50:32,000 --> 00:50:34,912
When he's got something on his mind,
he doesn't change his mind!

617
00:50:35,200 --> 00:50:37,634
And, it seems, he was
fond of the idea...

618
00:50:37,920 --> 00:50:39,797
... of me marrying that fool.

619
00:50:40,040 --> 00:50:42,998
At first he was gentle.
"My girl" and all that.

620
00:50:43,280 --> 00:50:45,157
"He's got so many ships!
He's got such a fortune!"

621
00:50:45,400 --> 00:50:46,469
"He's got so much money!"

622
00:50:46,640 --> 00:50:49,996
Then he changed tactics.

623
00:50:50,240 --> 00:50:51,593
"You'll marry him!"
"I won't!"

624
00:50:51,840 --> 00:50:53,239
"You'll marry him!"
"I won't!"

625
00:50:53,520 --> 00:50:54,589
"You will!"

626
00:50:54,840 --> 00:50:56,796
You hear me?
You'll marry him!

627
00:50:57,000 --> 00:50:59,275
You'll marry him
willy nilly!

628
00:50:59,520 --> 00:51:02,114
You're wrong if you think
I'll leave to the clutches...

629
00:51:02,320 --> 00:51:05,073
of fortune hunters! I haven't
worked as hard as I have...

630
00:51:05,320 --> 00:51:07,515
I haven't nearly
drowned in the seas...

631
00:51:07,720 --> 00:51:10,632
so that any given Dimitris
will find it all ready...

632
00:51:10,880 --> 00:51:12,996
... pretending to be cute
and in love!

633
00:51:13,280 --> 00:51:16,431
You're wrong! Dimitris didn't pretend
to be cute or in love!

634
00:51:16,680 --> 00:51:19,114
And I won't allow you
to talk to me like that!

635
00:51:19,400 --> 00:51:21,675
- What was that?
- What you heard!

636
00:51:23,160 --> 00:51:24,149
Oh!

637
00:51:24,560 --> 00:51:27,472
That was it! I left
the house that very night!

638
00:51:27,720 --> 00:51:29,676
But you took it too far!

639
00:51:29,880 --> 00:51:33,156
- What do you mean?
- He is your father, after all!

640
00:51:33,400 --> 00:51:36,631
If you push him too far,
he's going to be stubborn!

641
00:51:36,960 --> 00:51:40,794
These things require diplomacy.

642
00:51:41,080 --> 00:51:43,355
If l were you,
I'd do it differently.

643
00:51:43,680 --> 00:51:45,716
- What's that?
- I'd go to his office...

644
00:51:46,120 --> 00:51:48,759
knock on his door,
all polite like...

645
00:51:50,360 --> 00:51:51,713
Yes?

646
00:51:54,200 --> 00:51:55,679
<i>Good morninq, daddy. /</i>

647
00:51:55,960 --> 00:51:57,996
<i>First of all, here's</i>
<i>some flowers... </i>

648
00:51:58,240 --> 00:52:00,629
<i>... that I picked with my</i>
<i>own hands, just for you. /</i>

649
00:52:00,880 --> 00:52:02,916
- Thank you, child!
- </i>And I want you to listen to me. . </i>

650
00:52:03,200 --> 00:52:05,760
<i>... because I've qot</i>
<i>somethinq serious to tell you. </i>

651
00:52:07,600 --> 00:52:10,751
<i>You are my father and</i>
<i>I respect your opinion. </i>

652
00:52:11,000 --> 00:52:13,389
<i>I love and esteem</i>
<i>and respect you... </i>

653
00:52:13,680 --> 00:52:16,240
<i>but, I am a qirl... </i>

654
00:52:16,520 --> 00:52:19,318
<i>livinq in society and</i>
<i>as such, I have my preferences... </i>

655
00:52:19,560 --> 00:52:22,438
<i>... in matters</i>
<i>of... internal combustion, let's say. </i>

656
00:52:22,800 --> 00:52:25,712
<i>I mean, that the dude</i>
<i>you found is nice and all that... </i>

657
00:52:25,960 --> 00:52:29,555
<i>... but I don't like</i>
<i>his looks. </i>

658
00:52:30,120 --> 00:52:31,917
What would the old man
say to me then?

659
00:52:32,200 --> 00:52:34,270
"No, he's goodlooking
and you'll marry him?"

660
00:52:34,560 --> 00:52:38,075
And if he did, I'd still
be politely pushy.

661
00:52:38,360 --> 00:52:41,033
And in the end
I'd have got my wish.

662
00:52:41,320 --> 00:52:43,709
You don't know my father,
that's why you're talking like that.

663
00:52:44,000 --> 00:52:47,549
For him, words like heart,
emotion, love are foolish words.

664
00:52:47,840 --> 00:52:51,230
There's only one serious word
for him. The word "money".

665
00:52:51,520 --> 00:52:54,717
He esteems people according
to the money they have.

666
00:52:55,000 --> 00:52:57,116
He's divided people
into two categories.

667
00:52:57,400 --> 00:52:59,470
Those who have money
and those who don't.

668
00:52:59,720 --> 00:53:02,553
He appreciates the first
and despises the others.

669
00:53:02,840 --> 00:53:05,673
And... why am I telling
you all this?

670
00:53:06,240 --> 00:53:08,708
- Why should you care?
- Tell me something...

671
00:53:08,960 --> 00:53:11,793
What happened
to that young man?

672
00:53:12,080 --> 00:53:14,196
Dimitris? I told you,
he was transferred to Patras.

673
00:53:14,480 --> 00:53:16,869
He hasn't written?
He hasn't sent word?

674
00:53:17,160 --> 00:53:19,276
- Nothing...
- He just vanished?

675
00:53:19,520 --> 00:53:21,909
- Just like that...
- And now, miss Katie...

676
00:53:22,160 --> 00:53:24,754
if I may, let's say
that we are not...

677
00:53:25,040 --> 00:53:27,110
the cannibals you take us for...

678
00:53:27,360 --> 00:53:30,079
and let's say we forget
the fifty grand and tell you...

679
00:53:30,360 --> 00:53:33,670
"You may go", what will you do?
Where will you go?

680
00:53:33,920 --> 00:53:35,876
- I don't know...
- What does that mean?

681
00:53:36,120 --> 00:53:38,873
That's not right.
Are you to wander the fields?

682
00:53:39,160 --> 00:53:41,310
- Yes, I will just wander.
- Till when?

683
00:53:41,560 --> 00:53:43,471
Until I find the courage
to stop.

684
00:53:43,720 --> 00:53:46,757
And if we take
you back home, let's say?

685
00:53:47,040 --> 00:53:50,032
Then I'll find that
courage sooner!

686
00:53:52,360 --> 00:53:55,909
Stop crying.
Crying doesn't help.

687
00:53:56,240 --> 00:53:57,992
Stop crying
to see what's to be done.

688
00:53:58,280 --> 00:53:59,872
We all know
what's to be done.

689
00:54:00,120 --> 00:54:01,712
You'll turn me in
to the first policeman...

690
00:54:02,000 --> 00:54:03,433
He'll turn me over
to my father.

691
00:54:03,720 --> 00:54:06,188
You will collect the
fifty grand and I...

692
00:54:06,480 --> 00:54:08,675
I'll do what I will.

693
00:54:08,920 --> 00:54:11,514
What's left for me to do...

694
00:54:12,000 --> 00:54:13,638
That's not right, missy.

695
00:54:13,920 --> 00:54:16,434
Unfortunately, I don't
have fifty grand.

696
00:54:16,720 --> 00:54:19,314
If I did, I'd say
"Here's the fifty grand... "

697
00:54:19,600 --> 00:54:22,068
... "let me go in peace!"

698
00:54:22,320 --> 00:54:25,790
You see, I don't have the money
to buy my freedom.

699
00:54:26,080 --> 00:54:29,436
Just a minute, girl!
Isn't that laying it a bit too thick?

700
00:54:29,720 --> 00:54:32,996
Who do you think we are?
Bandits and kidnappers?

701
00:54:33,280 --> 00:54:35,589
We just...
What?

702
00:54:35,840 --> 00:54:37,717
- Policemen...
- Oops!

703
00:54:42,280 --> 00:54:44,157
- This is it!
- Go!

704
00:54:44,440 --> 00:54:46,510
- What?
- Leave, scram!

705
00:54:46,760 --> 00:54:48,830
