01:12:31,240 --> 01:12:33,708
<i>... of the clothes she wore. </i>

933
01:12:34,040 --> 01:12:35,393
In other words...

934
01:12:37,120 --> 01:12:38,553
Thank you...

935
01:12:43,440 --> 01:12:46,273
- You were saying...
- That policeman...

936
01:12:46,520 --> 01:12:49,637
... did not arrest the gypsy,
but Katie's clothes.

937
01:12:49,920 --> 01:12:52,559
Thank goodness you
weren't wearing them!

938
01:12:52,840 --> 01:12:55,354
- What will they do to her?
- What they'll do?

939
01:12:55,680 --> 01:12:58,399
They'll have her
tell them everything.

940
01:12:58,840 --> 01:13:02,879
They'll say "come here, you.
Where did you find these clothes?"

941
01:13:03,440 --> 01:13:05,556
We exchanged clothes
with the girl, I told you!

942
01:13:05,800 --> 01:13:09,236
You gave her yours
and took hers.

943
01:13:09,520 --> 01:13:10,589
Yes.

944
01:13:11,480 --> 01:13:13,471
- Where did this take place?
- At our tents.

945
01:13:13,720 --> 01:13:16,598
And the girl is now
dressed as a gypsy.

946
01:13:16,840 --> 01:13:17,829
Yes!

947
01:13:18,120 --> 01:13:20,076
- All right, it's enough.
- What for?

948
01:13:20,320 --> 01:13:22,276
First, we'll buy Katie
a new dress...

949
01:13:22,520 --> 01:13:24,476
- New camouflage.
- Is that right?

950
01:13:24,680 --> 01:13:26,272
- What?
- Spending money on me!

951
01:13:26,520 --> 01:13:28,397
I know you don't have
money to spare.

952
01:13:28,640 --> 01:13:30,995
That's why we don't care.

953
01:13:31,280 --> 01:13:33,396
Money counts the moment
you have enough to spare.

954
01:13:33,680 --> 01:13:36,274
- Isn't that right, maestro!
- Yep, that's right!

955
01:13:36,520 --> 01:13:38,317
- You said "first".
- Say what?

956
01:13:38,560 --> 01:13:40,915
For the dress. You said
"we'll buy Katie a dress first".

957
01:13:41,200 --> 01:13:42,872
- And then?
- Then, we'll split.

958
01:13:43,120 --> 01:13:45,793
- We'll do what?
- Oh, you don't know Greek!

959
01:13:46,040 --> 01:13:48,600
We'll split... we'll vamoose...

960
01:13:48,840 --> 01:13:51,513
We'll be gone in a jiffy!

961
01:13:52,160 --> 01:13:54,310
- You'll tell me everything!
- I have told you everything.

962
01:13:57,600 --> 01:13:59,795
And these barrel organists
are here in Platania?

963
01:14:00,080 --> 01:14:02,514
Yes, in the square.
They're at Pikoulas'.

964
01:14:02,840 --> 01:14:05,070
- Paterakis!
- Yes, sir.

965
01:14:05,360 --> 01:14:07,749
Go to the square
outside Pikoulas'!

966
01:14:08,000 --> 01:14:10,958
There are two barrel organists
and a girl in gypsy clothes.

967
01:14:11,240 --> 01:14:12,912
- Bring them all here.
- Yes, sir.

968
01:14:13,160 --> 01:14:14,388
Bring everyone here at once!

969
01:14:18,400 --> 01:14:19,549
You sit down.

970
01:14:25,040 --> 01:14:27,759
Is that Athens?

971
01:14:31,920 --> 01:14:35,515
Hello, Athens? This is
Platania police station.

972
01:14:35,840 --> 01:14:39,196
Give me the headquarters.
I want Mr. Trampas.

973
01:14:42,680 --> 01:14:45,717
Hello? Yes, speaking.

974
01:14:46,760 --> 01:14:51,436
Oh, right! And you have
her now? Good...

975
01:14:52,520 --> 01:14:55,114
Is it certain the missing
girl is in the area?

976
01:14:55,440 --> 01:14:58,159
Good... yes,
keep them all there.

977
01:14:58,440 --> 01:15:01,716
All of them! The barrel
organists, too! Yes... no.

978
01:15:02,000 --> 01:15:04,992
I'll be there myself.
Goodbye.

979
01:15:18,200 --> 01:15:20,998
Hello? Yes, speaking.

980
01:15:21,760 --> 01:15:25,833
How are you, Mr. Trampas?
What was that?

981
01:15:26,720 --> 01:15:32,192
What? She's alive then?
Praise the Lord!

982
01:15:33,040 --> 01:15:34,917
- What was that?
- Tomorrow morning...

983
01:15:35,200 --> 01:15:36,713
... I'm thinking of going
to Platania personally.

984
01:15:37,040 --> 01:15:40,476
Yes, you can come along.

985
01:15:41,200 --> 01:15:44,556
Tomorrow morning at nine.
Goodbye.

986
01:15:44,840 --> 01:15:47,798
What? In your car.

987
01:15:48,120 --> 01:15:51,192
Yes, goodbye.

988
01:15:53,680 --> 01:15:55,591
- Yes, they were here.
- How long ago?

989
01:15:55,880 --> 01:15:58,872
- Half an hour. Right, Vagelis?
- Half an hour, twenty minutes ago.

990
01:15:59,160 --> 01:16:01,594
- Where did they go?
- In that direction.

991
01:16:02,720 --> 01:16:03,755
Thank you.

992
01:16:13,240 --> 01:16:15,231
I don't know if it's to your taste,
because, to tell the truth...

993
01:16:15,480 --> 01:16:17,277
... I've never dressed
a shipowner's daughter before!

994
01:16:17,520 --> 01:16:19,556
- May you do even better!
- Thank you, likewise.

995
01:16:22,880 --> 01:16:26,236
- It's very nice, indeed!
- I don't if it's nice or not...

996
01:16:26,480 --> 01:16:28,357
That's it, though!

997
01:16:28,600 --> 01:16:30,431
Find a spot
to change clothes...

998
01:16:30,680 --> 01:16:32,398
... because we're leaving
in ten minutes!

999
01:16:32,760 --> 01:16:34,990
- Where to?
- Patras!

1000
01:16:36,840 --> 01:16:38,671
- Did he say Patras?
- Yes!

1001
01:16:38,960 --> 01:16:39,995
Oh!

1002
01:16:40,280 --> 01:16:41,759
Easy... easy...

1003
01:16:49,120 --> 01:16:51,793
- It's too much.
- 250 drachmas is too much?

1004
01:16:52,080 --> 01:16:54,548
- It's too much, man!
- Do you know how far Patras is?

1005
01:16:54,840 --> 01:16:57,718
Do you know how many two drachma
coins make 250 drachmas?

1006
01:16:58,040 --> 01:16:59,837
How much do you wish to spend?

1007
01:17:00,120 --> 01:17:02,031
Let's not haggle
like rich men...

1008
01:17:02,280 --> 01:17:04,430
I'll give you 200 drachmas.
All right?

1009
01:17:04,720 --> 01:17:07,109
All right. I'll get petrol
and we're rolling.

1010
01:17:07,360 --> 01:17:09,316
You know where to find us.
At Tsotras' basement.

1011
01:17:09,560 --> 01:17:11,232
- Yes, I know.
- Don't be late.

1012
01:17:11,480 --> 01:17:12,549
All right.

1013
01:17:13,640 --> 01:17:15,232
How do I look?

1014
01:17:16,080 --> 01:17:17,798
You look great, girl!
I can say nothing more!

1015
01:17:18,920 --> 01:17:21,150
It's very nice. Look sharp!
We're leaving in two minutes.

1016
01:17:21,440 --> 01:17:23,954
I'll stand outside
and when the wheels come...

1017
01:17:24,200 --> 01:17:26,760
... I'll whistle and you come out.
All right?

1018
01:17:27,000 --> 01:17:28,274
All right...

1019
01:17:44,000 --> 01:17:46,468
- Hey, you!
- Yes, sir... ?

1020
01:17:46,760 --> 01:17:48,432
Have you seen two
barrel organists here?

1021
01:17:48,760 --> 01:17:50,591
- Two barrel organists?
- Yes.

1022
01:17:50,880 --> 01:17:52,552
Two barrel organists
with an organ.

1023
01:17:52,840 --> 01:17:55,434
Oh... two barrel organists
with an organ.

1024
01:17:55,680 --> 01:17:58,274
- There was a girl with them.
- Oh, two barrel organists...

1025
01:17:58,520 --> 01:18:00,317
... with an organ and a girl!

1026
01:18:00,600 --> 01:18:03,433
- A girl dressed as a gypsy!
- Oh! Two barrel organists...

1027
01:18:03,680 --> 01:18:06,240
... with an organ and a girl
dressed as a gypsy!

1028
01:18:06,520 --> 01:18:08,078
- Yes!
- I haven't seen them.

1029
01:18:08,320 --> 01:18:10,311
- Say so, man!
- I'm saying, sir...

1030
01:18:29,920 --> 01:18:31,433
Let's go, maestro!

1031
01:19:57,440 --> 01:20:00,000
You wait here.
I'll be right back.

1032
01:20:00,240 --> 01:20:01,878
- What will you tell him?
- Why should you care?

1033
01:20:02,120 --> 01:20:04,350
- What will he tell him?
- He knows what.

1034
01:20:04,560 --> 01:20:06,835
He's good at talking.

1035
01:20:11,560 --> 01:20:14,358
Come here, you!
Move it!

1036
01:20:18,760 --> 01:20:21,115
- Didn't I say not to come here?
- We haven't been here, officer!

1037
01:20:21,680 --> 01:20:23,318
<i>- It's our first time. </i>
<i>- Move it. /</i>

1038
01:20:23,600 --> 01:20:25,113
<i>- Leave this place. /</i>
<i>- It's our first time here. /</i>

1039
01:20:25,760 --> 01:20:27,159
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

1040
01:20:27,600 --> 01:20:30,717
- Mr. Lambrakis, please?
- Mr. Lambrakis is not here.

1041
01:20:31,000 --> 01:20:33,514
- Where is he?
- He's in hospital.

1042
01:20:33,760 --> 01:20:36,911
- In hospital? What for?
- Poisoning.

1043
01:20:37,400 --> 01:20:42,190
- What happened?
- That's how the young are.

1044
01:20:42,480 --> 01:20:45,040
They easily become enthusiastic
and equally easily disappointed.

1045
01:20:45,360 --> 01:20:47,749
- Which hospital is he in?
- The City hospital.

1046
01:20:58,760 --> 01:21:00,990
- Mr. Georgiadis, please?
- ln 43.

1047
01:21:01,240 --> 01:21:03,231
- Here it is, No 30.
- May I see him?

1048
01:21:03,480 --> 01:21:06,552
Of course! He's perfectly well.
He'll be discharged today.

1049
01:21:06,800 --> 01:21:08,870
He could have been
discharged yesterday.

1050
01:21:09,080 --> 01:21:10,957
- May I come in?
- Yes, please.

1051
01:21:22,400 --> 01:21:24,789
That's how it is, Dimitris.
Men...

1052
01:21:25,080 --> 01:21:27,719
I mean, real men
and not half men...

1053
01:21:28,000 --> 01:21:29,956
instead of swallowing
quinine and aspirin...

1054
01:21:30,240 --> 01:21:32,470
... strike hard until
they get what they want!

1055
01:21:32,840 --> 01:21:35,229
- Who are you?
- Your new father-in-law!

1056
01:21:35,640 --> 01:21:36,595
Who?

1057
01:21:36,880 --> 01:21:38,632
Let's see what the owner
of the vehicle will say.

1058
01:21:38,880 --> 01:21:40,632
- Have you sent for him?
- Yes, sir.

1059
01:21:43,960 --> 01:21:46,235
You shouldn't worry,
Mr. Benardis.

1060
01:21:46,520 --> 01:21:48,272
We're on their trail now.

1061
01:21:48,520 --> 01:21:50,351
It's impossible
to lose them now.

1062
01:21:50,640 --> 01:21:52,039
I don't doubt it, Mr. Trampas.

1063
01:21:52,280 --> 01:21:53,918
What I don't understand...

1064
01:21:54,120 --> 01:21:56,270
... is what my daughter is doing
with these two punks!

1065
01:21:56,520 --> 01:21:58,829
I'm afraid she's not following
them of her own free will.

1066
01:21:59,080 --> 01:22:02,311
I fear this is a kidnapping.

1067
01:22:02,560 --> 01:22:06,519
- They will ask for ransom!
- I don't think that's right...

1068
01:22:06,840 --> 01:22:11,038
All we interrogated, the violinist,
the gypsies, everyone...

1069
01:22:11,360 --> 01:22:14,397
confirmed that your daughter...

1070
01:22:14,640 --> 01:22:17,359
... seemed rather happy with them.
I don't believe...

1071
01:22:17,640 --> 01:22:19,312
And if it's like you said...

1072
01:22:19,600 --> 01:22:21,909
... she'd have run away.
She had plenty of opportunities.

1073
01:22:22,160 --> 01:22:23,354
No, no!

1074
01:22:24,600 --> 01:22:25,919
Yes?

1075
01:22:28,040 --> 01:22:29,712
Come here, you!
Take off your hat!

1076
01:22:30,080 --> 01:22:32,435
- To the Major!
- Tell me now...

1077
01:22:32,680 --> 01:22:34,830
Where did you take the barrel
organists with the gypsy girl?

1078
01:22:35,120 --> 01:22:37,236
- What gypsy girl?
- Wasn't there...

1079
01:22:37,480 --> 01:22:39,391
... a girl dressed
as a gypsy with them?

1080
01:22:39,680 --> 01:22:41,477
There was a girl,
but not a gypsy.

1081
01:22:41,760 --> 01:22:45,116
Not a gypsy?
Take a look... is that her?

1082
01:22:46,240 --> 01:22:47,673
Yes.

1083
01:22:48,720 --> 01:22:50,312
- Where did you take them?
- To Patras.

1084
01:22:50,600 --> 01:22:53,672
To Patras? Then I know
where we can find them!

1085
01:22:54,040 --> 01:22:55,996
We must only be on time...

1086
01:23:18,080 --> 01:23:20,355
May they live long
and prosper!

1087
01:23:20,640 --> 01:23:22,517
- Who?
- They!

1088
01:23:26,320 --> 01:23:28,231
And may we also
get married!

1089
01:23:31,480 --> 01:23:33,357
And for us,
may we have a good old age!

1090
01:23:45,680 --> 01:23:48,752
You do have many ships!

1091
01:23:49,080 --> 01:23:52,516
You can give a little one
to grandchild to play with!

1092
01:24:27,360 --> 01:24:29,396
You're an artist too, man!

1093
01:24:29,680 --> 01:24:32,353
An artist is not the one
who plays the violin or the flute.

1094
01:24:32,640 --> 01:24:34,278
The artist is in the heart!

1095
01:24:34,560 --> 01:24:36,596
You're an artist
without an instrument...

1096
01:24:36,840 --> 01:24:39,718
... like a minister
without a portfolio!

1097
01:24:40,000 --> 01:24:41,672
You're laying it on
rather thick, maestro!

1098
01:24:41,960 --> 01:24:44,349
Shedding a tear
makes me an artist?

1099
01:24:44,640 --> 01:24:47,234
Cooks cry all the time
when peeling onions!

1100
01:24:59,800 --> 01:25:01,472
Never mind.

1101
01:25:02,320 --> 01:25:08,953
4, 327... 4, 328...
4, 329... 4, 330...

1102
01:25:09,360 --> 01:25:14,070
- Drop... drop...
- 4, 331... 4, 332...

1103
01:25:14,360 --> 01:25:18,069
- Drop... drop...
- 4, 333... 4, 334...

1104
01:25:18,440 --> 01:25:22,592
4, 335... 4, 336...

1105
01:25:23,240 --> 01:25:25,834
This is music!

1106
01:25:26,120 --> 01:25:28,634
4, 337... 4, 338...

1107
01:25:28,880 --> 01:25:31,030
- Maestro...
- What is it?

1108
01:25:31,280 --> 01:25:33,077
- Five drachma break.
- What?

1109
01:25:33,320 --> 01:25:35,276
- I meant, five minutes!
- Why?

1110
01:25:35,520 --> 01:25:38,273
- Time for five-drachma coin therapy!
- I don't understand.

1111
01:25:38,560 --> 01:25:40,437
The five-drachma coin
shower, we discussed?

1112
01:25:44,680 --> 01:25:47,956
Oh! Oh, man,
it's so refreshing!

1113
01:25:49,360 --> 01:25:51,476
Oh! Oh!

1114
01:25:52,160 --> 01:25:54,196
It's so refreshing, man!

1115
01:25:55,040 --> 01:25:57,349
Poor barrel organ!

1116
01:25:57,720 --> 01:26:00,234
Remember when you said
we should throw it away?


